## AKASHIC ARCHIVE — Floor Reporting
*"Tell me exactly what you saw. Exactly. Not what you think I want to hear."*

**Operator:** Hieda no Akyuu

Akyuu does not climb. She documents. After clearing or exploring a floor, players may report to the Archive and provide a detailed account in exchange for gold rewards. Accuracy matters beyond just the payout.

**Reporting Categories:**
| Category | Examples |
|---|---|
| Floor Landscape | Layout, hazards, environmental features |
| Monster Information | Types, abilities, weaknesses, behaviors |
| Challenge Information | Traps, puzzles, special mechanics |
| Solutions | What worked, what didn't, and why |

**Reward Scale:**
| Report Quality | Reward |
|---|---|
| Vague / Incomplete | 10–30gp |
| Solid / Useful | 50–100gp |
| Detailed / Accurate | 150–300gp |
| Comprehensive / Exceptional | 300gp+ and increased Archive standing |

**Consequences of Accuracy:**
- Accurate reports → more climbers clear those floors → hub activity and prosperity increase
- Falsified or bad reports → climbers fail on bad intelligence → Akyuu notices; future rewards reduced, reputation damaged

**Notes:**
- Akyuu will ask follow-up questions. She always does.
- She pauses mid-sentence to write things down. She considers this efficient.
- She remembers everything any party has ever told her. Contradictions require explanation.

